OL,3,C'Swatting' hoax caller who faked
OL,4,Chostage situation sentenced
OL,6,FHe claimed he would execute the first
OL,7,Fhostage "within 15 minutes" unless he
OL,8,Freceived 15,000 dollars (#12,000) in
OL,9,Fcash.
OL,11,FThe Swat team then went to the address
OL,12,Fbelieving the threat to be real.
OL,14,FHannah Sidaway, specialist prosecutor
OL,15,Ffor CPS West Midlands, said: "Swatting
OL,16,Fis far more than a crude prank, it is
OL,17,Fa serious crime which can have
OL,18,Fdevastating consequences.
